WHEN a video of them pouring their hearts on the music decks emerged on social media a stream of questions flooded in with everyone eager to know who the talents were. It was crystal clear from the admiring comments that they carried out the energy that the entertainment industry relished. After solidifying their names in the entertainment industry no introduction was needed, people knew it is the ever vim and vigour TxC. Tarryn Reid, 25, and Clairise Hefke, 27, make up the dynamic global sensation DJ duo TxC. Having graced many places around South Africa and on global stages, the duo made their first piece of work. The Port Elizabeth born talents have confirmed the release of their debut amapiano EP titled A fierce piano, set to take place on June 24. A FIERCE PIANO is a 5 track EP featuring eminent artists and producers including Unlimited Soul, Daliwonga, Murumba Pitch & Toss. Speaking about their offering they said it was scary yet thrilling thing to do. “It was quite exciting and scary at the same time because it was our first time doing this. It was our first time getting people in the studio and having to relate ideas,” affirmed the duo. Asked about the essence of the EP they said: We started our EP beginning of the year. It was quite a journey discovering what our sound will be and which sound we are going to identify with. And we have been in the industry for a while and so people were expecting a certain sound from us. So the sound that we chose to go for on our EP was more soulful.” “We have found a unique sound that works for us, and this EP is a reflection of that. We hope you love it as much as we do.” The duo have also showcased their artistry in the UK, Dubai, Tanzania, Kenya, Ghana, Namibia, Angola, Uganda and Mozambique among other countries.